ABOUT US Xenon4pay is a mobile wallet service provider, founded in 2016, for payment and retail solutions. Our aim is to make carrying money and making payments much easier while keeping it secure and convenient. We design and deliver mobile wallet applications that connect businesses – no matter what industry – to their customers in realtime. We are working towards building a complete ecosystem where mobile wallet users can use their smartphone for paying all the bills whether in outlets or online or even transfer from wallet to wallet, making it safer and more convenient. close
Help 1. What is Bookeey? Why should I use it? Bookeey is a Mobile Wallet App. It is the quickest, most convenient, and safest mobile wallet for Shopping, Mobile recharge, Money transfers, Bill Payments and lot more. Use Bookeey for a cashless, hassle-free experience while shopping, dining and out&around! 2. How does Bookeey wallet work? Bookeey wallet is secure pseudo wallet which allows you to top up wallet via online Payment gateway and currently allows you to make payments in partner shops, send money to other Bookeey wallet users, purchase virtual prepaid cards such as iTunes, PlayStation, etc., send international airtime, view and save merchant offers, and much more to come! \n \n Currently Bookeey wallet supports amount in KD. 3. How can I create a Bookeey account? First download Bookeey wallet app from your respective mobile device app store.\n \n To register fill in the requested info and attach front and back images of your Civil ID card.\n \n Make sure to correctly enter your email address because all our communications with you will be by email!\n \n Submit the info and wait till Bookeey activates your accounts, this may take upto 24 hrs. \n \n When account is activated you will receive an OTP (One Time Password) by email to the email address you registered with. \n \n Login to the App using this OTP and change your password. 4. Why I have to scan my Civil ID? Bookeey as a financial service complies with the mandatory KYC process followed by the Kuwaiti Banks; however, your information is safe with us since it is encrypted and kept in a secured database for official use if & when needed. 5. I registered but did not receive my Password? Since the information provided will be checked manually by our staff to ensure proper KYC process, it may take up to 24 hours for you to receive your password on your registered email address, please call us on 22023232 if you did not receive the email after 24 hours. 6. Where would I use my password? You will use your password to login to the "BookeeyWallet" App and login to your website portal. 7. What is the password policy? For enhanced security, we made the password 7 characters which should include at least one numeric, one letter, and one special character. 8. What if I forgot my password? Don\'t worry! you can reset your password by clicking on "forgot password" on the login page. after con-firming to reset the password, you will receive an OTP (One Time Password) by email on the email ad-dress you registered with, login using this password and change it to your own password. 9. How to change my Password? You can change your Password from the menu available at the top right corner of the App : change Password option 10. What is TPIN? TPIN is a 4 digit Transaction PIN. you will need it to complete transactions higher than 5KD. 11. Why I need TPIN & Password? Password is used for login to the App, for extra in-App security we introduced TPIN for transactions over 5 KD. 12. How to add money to the wallet? Login to the Bookeey wallet and click on \'Load Wallet\'. You will be redirected to a secured \'Payment Gateway\' page. Use any debit card issued by any Bank in State of Kuwait and load you wallet. Since this is a secure gateway provided by KNET, your Bank details cannot be viewed by Bookeey. You can confirm the same with your own bank as well.
13. Is there any registration fee? It\'s absolutely free! And No hidden charges! You can become a BookeeyWallet user for free, there is also no additional costs to load wallet, pay , money transfer & Bill payments. 14. Is my account information safe? Don\'t worry! All information transmitted between you and Bookeey is done through a secured channel in an encrypted form. Bookeey will never release any of your details to anyone. 15. How quickly does the top up get to the phone? It\'s just a matter of few seconds! That\'s why it is the "fastest" way to mobile freedom.
16. Top up unsuccessful! Where is my money? Here are some possible reasons:\n \n 1- You have just loaded your wallet but did not submit the request properly.\n \n
2- You did not enter the KnetOTP on time so the Load request failed.\n \n
3- There was a delay from Knet end and thus Bookeey is unable to confirm your load.\n \n
4- internet Connectivity issues due to which top-up was stalled.\n \n
No problem! We are here for you. We will communicate with KNET on behalf of you to refund the money back to the same bank account you have used for funding the Top-up, afterall KNET tracks all the Load transactions.
17. I want to load wallet and the KNET page is asking for the OTP (one time pass), what is this? The KnetOTP was introduced by Knet as additional security for online transactions. when submitting an order online thru KNET gateways, you will receive a SMS from KnetOTP on the mobile no. registered with your Bank . the SMS will include a 6 digits code OTP. Use this code within 4 minutes otherwise this code will expire and you should re-submit your request.\n \n Check your messages on your phone to get the KnetOTP. If not received check with your bank to update your mobile no. 18. I am waiting! How much time will you take to solve my query? Call our helpdesk on 22023232 and we will assist you. 19. I have a feedback for you! How can I reach you? Your suggestions are extremely valuable; please communicate with us via: customercare@bookeey.com
20. My money has been debited from bank account! Where has it gone? Don\'t worry. Please wait for another 10 minutes.\n \n If your wallet balance was not updated after 10 min, please call our helpdesk on 22023232. 21. While doing a recharge on Bookeey I received an error, why? You may get errors if: \n \n 1- Entered a wrong mobile plan type or entered wrong bill details \n \n
2- Trying to recharge with wrong denominations \n \n
3- The service is temporarily unavailable on App \n \n In such cases, We suggest you to double check the details you have entered and try again! 22. I mistakenly recharged on wrong number! Can I get my money back? That’s sad! Unfortunately, recharge once successful cannot be reversed. We request you to get in touch with your mobile operator for help. 23. I recharged and received successful message on App but did not receive the recharge credit? Just wait few more minutes, if still did not get your recharge credit, call your operator and present the recharge code you received on the transaction details. 24. Is it necessary to add money to the wallet? There is no minimum balance required to keep the wallet active, however If you want to make any transactions on the BookeeyWallet App you should load your wallet because BookeeyWallet is a prepaid service. 25. How can I check my wallet balance? Just to the right side of upper blue strip, current balance is shown. 26. Is it secure to Load Bookeey wallet? It\'s absolutely secure! KNET is our payment gateway partner. All the transactions are executed safely over a secured page and no personal information regarding your payment is ever accessible to any employee or third party. 27. I was redirected to KNET page! What is a payment gateway? It\'s completely safe & secure. Payment gateway is an online payment service provided by KNET for online portals to provide you a secured internet based payment options. 28. What happens to my balance if I don’t use my wallet for some time? Your money is safe with us! Your wallet will not be inactive or dormant, use your balance whenever you want! 29. How do I change my device but continue with the same mobile number? Please install BookeeyWallet app on your new device and enter your mobile number. \n \n When system detects that a new device trying to login to existing mobile wallet will prompt to confirm “change device”, after confirmation you should enter current Password and Civil ID no. for the system to authenticate your data. Afterall your balance is tied to the mobile no. and no one should be able to use another device to access your wallet! 30. Do I have a web portal access to view my transactions history? You need to use your Bookeey wallet login credentials to access your Bookeey account online. Your mobile no is your username and password is the same password you use to login to the App. Visit our website: www.bookeey.com and click on customer login on the top right corner to access your portal. 31. Can I have multiple wallets? It is not possible to have multiple wallets. During registration it is not possible to use same Civil ID for registering another mobile no., it you need multiple wallets for family members you can register their mobile numbers using their own Civil IDs. Close
